## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb7a5-177">Questa proprietà recupera solo le stringhe di sostituzione per la voce.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb7a5-177">This property retrieves only the replacement strings for the entry.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb7a5-178">Per recuperare il messaggio completo, leggere la <xref:System.Diagnostics.EventLogEntry.Message%2A> proprietà.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb7a5-178">To retrieve the full message, read the <xref:System.Diagnostics.EventLogEntry.Message%2A> property.</span></span>  

 <span data-ttu-id="eb7a5-179">Il <xref:System.Diagnostics.EventLogEntry.ReplacementStrings%2A> proprietà contiene le versioni localizzate di stringhe di sostituzione che vengono utilizzate nella voce del registro eventi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb7a5-179">The <xref:System.Diagnostics.EventLogEntry.ReplacementStrings%2A> property contains the localized versions of replacement strings that are used in the event log entry.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb7a5-180">Se si specifica il file di risorse che contengono le stringhe in ciascuna lingua di destinazione per l'applicazione, è possibile trasmettere i messaggi del registro eventi nella lingua utilizzata nel computer.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb7a5-180">If you provide resource files that contain strings in each target language for your application, you can emit event log messages in the language that is used on that computer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb7a5-181">A tale scopo, creare un'istanza di <xref:System.Resources.ResourceManager> classe per l'assembly delle risorse che contiene le stringhe di sostituzione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb7a5-181">To do that, create an instance of the <xref:System.Resources.ResourceManager> class for the resource assembly that contains your replacement strings.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb7a5-182">Il primo parametro del <xref:System.Resources.ResourceManager.%23ctor%28System.String%2CSystem.Reflection.Assembly%29> costruttore identifica l'assembly delle risorse da utilizzare.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb7a5-182">The first parameter of the <xref:System.Resources.ResourceManager.%23ctor%28System.String%2CSystem.Reflection.Assembly%29> constructor identifies the resource assembly to be used.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb7a5-183">Utilizzare il <xref:System.Resources.ResourceManager.GetString%2A> metodo di istanza per fornire messaggi localizzati per gli eventi di log.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb7a5-183">Use the <xref:System.Resources.ResourceManager.GetString%2A> method of that instance to supply localized messages for log events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb7a5-184">Il codice seguente imposta automaticamente il messaggio per la lingua per le impostazioni cultura correnti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb7a5-184">The following code automatically sets the message to the language for the current culture.</span></span>  

```  
ResourceManager LocRM = new ResourceManager("ReplacementStrings.TestStrings",   
      typeof(Program).Assembly);  
EventLog e1 = new EventLog("LocTest", "MyMachine", "LocTest");  
// Get the string associated with the current culture.  
e1.WriteEntry(LocRM.GetString("strMessage"),  
   EventLogEntryType.Information);  
```
